-- Brazil Treasury may lend $13.5 bln to BNDES this year - source
-- By Luciana Otoni
-- Mon May 12, 2014 04:28PM EDT
-- None



BRASILIA, May 12 (Reuters) - Brazil's Treasury is negotiating lending about 30 billion reais ($13.52 billion) to state-run development bank BNDES [BNDES.UL] this year, a source at the Finance Ministry told Reuters on Monday.  ($1 = 2.2192 Brazilian reais)   (Reporting by Luciana Otoni; Writing by Alonso Soto)  ((alonso.soto@thomsonreuters.com)(+55-61-3426-7027)(Reuters Messaging: alonso.soto.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: BRAZIL ECONOMY/TREASURY

